&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Tucson needed to avoid falling into the same trap that Magmatron fell into.
&gt; He had been warned before about his temper and now was the true test of
&gt; control.  He shakes his head to try and knock some sense into himself, which
&gt; he was finding very hard to do.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; You&#39;re right Big Convoy, I shouldn&#39;t be as aggressive as I am, I&#39;m just
&gt; extremely frustrated by the fact that I can&#39;t pull Rodimus out of corruption
&gt; as I hoped to the first time I rescued him.  What I really need is guidance,
&gt; not violence.  But in order to attempt another recovery, I will have to
&gt; fight him. I must knock whatever it is that&#39;s controlling him out of his
&gt; internal programming.  By some form of strong impact, I may be able to
&gt; jostle something loose to enable Rodimus to regain control of his own logic
&gt; circuitry.     Then I have to get him to surrender the matrix for safe
&gt; keeping until such time Rodimus is free of his invasive programming..  Thank
&gt; you for stopping me by the way, I&#39;m glad you were honest with me.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

There was a nod from CONVOY, in the darkness it was just his optics
glowing brightly as he moved his head. &quot;We all have lessons to learn,
you are young yet.&quot;

There was a click on the floor and then a thunk and then light began
to pour into the cell, it was coming from a hole int he floor that had
not been there before.

&quot;Who is this?&quot; Said a figure standing in the hole, he was colored in
various shades of blue, gray, red, and yellow, and was slender yet
seemingly agile.

BIG CONVOY sighed, &quot;Night Viper, meet Tuscon.&quot; BIG gestured between
TUSCON and this new comer, &quot;And Tuscon, this is our resident escape
artist Night Viper.&quot;

&quot;Slag!&quot; NIGHT VIPER said as he glanced at TUSCON, &quot;We don&#39;t have time
for this.&quot; He was obviously talking to BIG CONVOY and annoyed at
having TUSCON there.

BIG glanced at NIGHT VIPER, &quot;I&#39;ll vouch for him.&quot; He said, his deep
voice quiet as a whisper.

There was a nod from NIGHT VIPER as he looked at TUSCON, &quot;Well come on
then, this way!&quot; He disappeared back through the hole, a hole just big
enough for the likes of BIG CONVOY and TUSCON to fit through. &quot;And
watch your step.&quot; He added.

